291
00:14:16,280 --> 00:14:19,280
Surveying the sky and gazing at a thousand milky ways.

292
00:14:21,040 --> 00:14:24,370
Mr. Qian took 'surveying the sky' and named it 'aerospace'.

293
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:27,960
Past expectations fulfilled today.

294
00:14:37,640 --> 00:14:39,120
Everyone has worked hard recently.

295
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:40,120
Starting tomorrow,

296
00:14:40,120 --> 00:14:42,440
Longzhou-1 will be resupplied.

297
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:44,920
We can take a rest.

298
00:14:50,920 --> 00:14:51,760
Everyone,

299
00:14:51,760 --> 00:14:53,440
after the work handover,

300
00:14:53,440 --> 00:14:54,600
let's go to the meeting room.

301
00:14:54,600 --> 00:14:55,930
I have something to say.

302
00:14:56,160 --> 00:14:56,800
Okay.

303
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:00,120
I didn't expect this handover to be so thrilling.

304
00:15:00,120 --> 00:15:00,720
Yeah.

305
00:15:00,720 --> 00:15:01,440
Our country

306
00:15:01,440 --> 00:15:04,440
has finally overcome another technical difficulty.

307
00:15:21,920 --> 00:15:23,560
Watching the maiden launch for the first time,

308
00:15:23,560 --> 00:15:25,490
do you have any specific feelings?

309
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:27,280
Specifically?

310
00:15:27,920 --> 00:15:29,800
I can sincerely feel that

311
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:30,800
being a Star Herder

312
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:32,440
is incredibly romantic,

313
00:15:32,440 --> 00:15:33,760
incredibly happy,

314
00:15:33,760 --> 00:15:35,090
and incredibly joyful.

315
00:15:35,560 --> 00:15:36,600
I will keep working hard

316
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:38,260
to be a qualified Star Herder.

317
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:39,720
Indeed.

318
00:15:40,320 --> 00:15:42,520
Catching the maiden launch right after arriving

319
00:15:42,520 --> 00:15:43,680
is quite lucky.

320
00:15:43,920 --> 00:15:45,480
But I hope you understand

321
00:15:45,840 --> 00:15:48,240
that this luck is just an unexpected bonus.

322
00:15:48,800 --> 00:15:50,520
As a scientific worker,

323
00:15:50,520 --> 00:15:53,000
what's more important is a rigorous attitude

324
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:54,460
and professional skills.

325
00:15:59,800 --> 00:16:00,960
To you,

326
00:16:01,120 --> 00:16:03,600
this is just a thrilling show.

327
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:05,200
But if you really want to become

328
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:06,840
a qualified Star Herder,

329
00:16:07,040 --> 00:16:08,160
I hope everyone

330
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:09,920
first understands

331
00:16:09,920 --> 00:16:12,640
the responsibilities on your shoulders.

332
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:19,280
Although there were twists and turns this time,

333
00:16:19,280 --> 00:16:20,610
it was also meaningful.

334
00:16:21,560 --> 00:16:24,040
I didn't expect my curtain call speech

335
00:16:25,920 --> 00:16:27,280
to be addressed to you.

336
00:16:31,920 --> 00:16:33,520
Curtain call speech?

337
00:16:34,240 --> 00:16:35,000
Hou.

338
00:16:35,520 --> 00:16:36,520
What do you mean?

339
00:16:37,840 --> 00:16:38,680
Nothing.

340
00:16:40,120 --> 00:16:42,240
This is my last mission.

341
00:16:42,640 --> 00:16:44,560
I didn't want to leave any regrets.

342
00:16:44,560 --> 00:16:46,960
Unexpectedly, there were still mistakes.

343
00:16:47,440 --> 00:16:48,560
No, Hou,

344
00:16:48,760 --> 00:16:50,200
are you resigning?

345
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:52,770
After this mission is done,

346
00:16:54,560 --> 00:16:55,400
I'll be leaving.

347
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:57,680
Did Mr. Qin approve it?

348
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:03,930
What's going on?

349
00:17:05,920 --> 00:17:06,560
All right.

350
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:08,520
This part of the work is over.

351
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:09,720
You can go back first.

352
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,160
For subsequent work,

353
00:17:11,160 --> 00:17:12,359
you will be notified.

354
00:17:14,560 --> 00:17:15,200
Wait.

355
00:17:17,160 --> 00:17:18,119
I'm sorry.

356
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:21,440
It's your first time observing,

357
00:17:21,599 --> 00:17:23,329
and we made a fool of ourselves.

358
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:24,800
No, well,

359
00:17:25,119 --> 00:17:26,000
let's go.

360
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:39,680
Hou,

361
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:41,200
what does this mean?

362
00:17:43,720 --> 00:17:44,400
Jiajia.

363
00:17:46,240 --> 00:17:48,560
You know my family situation.

364
00:17:48,760 --> 00:17:51,020
My wife is about to have our second child.

365
00:17:53,400 --> 00:17:54,320
The economy,

366
00:17:54,320 --> 00:17:56,360
and pressure from all sides is quite heavy.

367
00:17:56,360 --> 00:17:58,920
I want to find a job with more regular hours,

368
00:17:59,320 --> 00:18:00,320
or rather,

369
00:18:00,320 --> 00:18:02,800
a job that can give my family a better life.

370
00:18:03,600 --> 00:18:04,320
Hou,

371
00:18:04,480 --> 00:18:05,920
didn't you say before

372
00:18:06,160 --> 00:18:08,760
that your dream was to be a Star Herder forever?

373
00:18:09,120 --> 00:18:10,000
How could...

374
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:10,680
Yeah.

375
00:18:11,480 --> 00:18:12,920
So many years of dreams,

376
00:18:13,240 --> 00:18:14,640
so many years of passion,

377
00:18:14,880 --> 00:18:16,010
I remember them all.

378
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:18,660
Since you chose this path,

379
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:20,650
you have to stick with it to the end.

380
00:18:21,720 --> 00:18:22,720
For so many years,

381
00:18:22,960 --> 00:18:25,240
how many times when I wanted to give up...

382
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:27,920
It's all because of this self-inspiration

383
00:18:27,920 --> 00:18:29,450
that I've held on until now.

384
00:18:35,640 --> 00:18:36,320
Old Hou.

385
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:39,460
I still remember when I first joined,

386
00:18:39,560 --> 00:18:40,720
what you told me.

387
00:18:41,280 --> 00:18:43,080
You said as long as we keep trying,

388
00:18:43,080 --> 00:18:44,880
we will definitely see the dawn.

389
00:18:45,520 --> 00:18:47,480
We've all held on for so long.

390
00:18:47,920 --> 00:18:50,120
The Haoyue-4 mission is about to start,

391
00:18:50,880 --> 00:18:52,320
landing on the far side of the moon.

392
00:18:52,320 --> 00:18:53,800
This is not just for us,

393
00:18:54,040 --> 00:18:56,440
but humanity's challenge to the universe.

394
00:18:57,480 --> 00:18:58,680
Just stay.

395
00:19:01,320 --> 00:19:02,080
Jiajia.

396
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:04,360
It's not that I don't want to hold on.

397
00:19:04,360 --> 00:19:05,560
Whenever I close my eyes,

398
00:19:05,560 --> 00:19:07,520
all I see are accidents and failures.

399
00:19:07,520 --> 00:19:08,440
Just now,

400
00:19:08,880 --> 00:19:10,880
when the docking almost went wrong,

401
00:19:10,880 --> 00:19:13,080
I've dreamed about it so many times.

402
00:19:13,080 --> 00:19:14,120
Work ID.

403
00:19:18,440 --> 00:19:21,000
You must have put too much pressure on yourself.

404
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:22,640
You just need some rest.

405
00:19:24,400 --> 00:19:25,480
Actually,

406
00:19:25,880 --> 00:19:27,440
those kids

407
00:19:27,440 --> 00:19:28,560
are right.

408
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:30,800
Being a star-herder

409
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:35,320
is happy, lucky, and romantic.

410
00:19:36,240 --> 00:19:37,480
But now,

411
00:19:39,520 --> 00:19:40,320
I'm sorry,

412
00:19:42,800 --> 00:19:43,800
I'm deserting.

413
00:19:53,320 --> 00:19:54,000
Old Hou.

414
00:19:54,760 --> 00:19:56,960
There's nothing to be ashamed of.

415
00:19:58,080 --> 00:19:59,280
It's your choice.

416
00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:01,090
I won't say more.

417
00:20:02,440 --> 00:20:04,300
I'll submit the report tomorrow.

418
00:20:05,640 --> 00:20:06,320
Everyone.

419
00:20:07,800 --> 00:20:08,930
For all these years,

420
00:20:09,160 --> 00:20:10,280
I thank you all

421
00:20:10,520 --> 00:20:12,080
for your support and help.

422
00:20:14,960 --> 00:20:15,960
Thank you.

423
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:43,520
You're here just to cause trouble

424
00:21:43,520 --> 00:21:44,780
and play games, right?

425
00:21:49,280 --> 00:21:51,940
Weren't you quite ambitious when you were a kid?

426
00:21:52,480 --> 00:21:54,340
Why have you become like this now?

427
00:22:00,720 --> 00:22:01,400
Stop pretending.

428
00:22:01,400 --> 00:22:02,240
You're connected to the TV,

429
00:22:02,240 --> 00:22:03,840
you've been dead for a while.

430
00:22:07,360 --> 00:22:09,200
I'm advising you out of kindness.

431
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:10,400
How lucky you are

432
00:22:10,400 --> 00:22:12,530
to see the launch right after joining.

433
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:14,400
Why don't you cherish it?

434
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:17,440
Besides, you're still in the probation period.

435
00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:18,520
If you can't become a regular employee,

436
00:22:18,520 --> 00:22:19,520
it would be a pity.

437
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:22,880
Does it have anything to do with you?

438
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:24,400
Of course it does.

439
00:22:24,400 --> 00:22:24,880
Do you know

440
00:22:24,880 --> 00:22:26,240
how many people's spots you're taking?

441
00:22:26,240 --> 00:22:27,200
How many opportunities?

442
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:28,680
How many people want to come but can't?

443
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:29,840
Why don't you cherish it?

444
00:22:29,840 --> 00:22:31,100
Even if I don't take it,

445
00:22:31,160 --> 00:22:33,160
the opportunity might not be yours.

446
00:22:38,360 --> 00:22:39,960
You don't need to provoke me.

447
00:22:40,160 --> 00:22:42,220
I don't need to prove anything to you.

448
00:22:43,720 --> 00:22:44,560
You're all here.

449
00:22:44,560 --> 00:22:45,440
That's great.

450
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:46,920
Want to play online

451
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:47,960
and relax a bit?

452
00:22:48,040 --> 00:22:48,970
Why are you here?

453
00:22:49,560 --> 00:22:50,240
Wei.

454
00:22:50,440 --> 00:22:51,240
You have no idea

455
00:22:51,240 --> 00:22:53,200
how exciting and thrilling today was.

456
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:54,600
I'm still in a daze.

457
00:22:54,600 --> 00:22:56,000
I really need to wake up.

458
00:22:56,040 --> 00:22:57,900
Do you want to play a match with me?

459
00:22:59,640 --> 00:23:00,640
Play by yourself.

460
00:23:02,680 --> 00:23:04,540
Is the archive room this busy too?

461
00:23:07,480 --> 00:23:08,360
I'll play with you.

462
00:23:08,360 --> 00:23:09,690
What do you want to play?

463
00:23:10,880 --> 00:23:11,720
Anything is fine.

464
00:23:11,720 --> 00:23:12,720
It's up to you, Qi.

465
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:29,440
Mr. Qin.

466
00:23:29,880 --> 00:23:30,440
Jiajia.

467
00:23:30,880 --> 00:23:31,760
Come.

468
00:23:32,160 --> 00:23:32,760
Okay.

469
00:23:36,800 --> 00:23:37,560
Mr. Qin.

470
00:23:38,360 --> 00:23:39,360
About Old Hou.

471
00:23:39,360 --> 00:23:41,880
I approved his resignation report.

472
00:23:42,280 --> 00:23:43,280
I didn't tell you

473
00:23:43,280 --> 00:23:44,200
because

474
00:23:44,200 --> 00:23:46,280
I was afraid it would affect your mood.

475
00:23:46,280 --> 00:23:48,010
This is also his own intention.

476
00:23:48,880 --> 00:23:50,400
About this matter,

477
00:23:50,400 --> 00:23:52,330
I don't want you to have any burden.

478
00:23:53,800 --> 00:23:54,480
It's fine.

479
00:23:54,880 --> 00:23:56,520
Since this is his choice,

480
00:23:56,520 --> 00:23:57,920
there's nothing I can do.

481
00:23:59,040 --> 00:24:00,840
But with Old Hou gone,

482
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:02,200
I'm short-handed.

483
00:24:02,520 --> 00:24:03,320
Haoyue-4

484
00:24:03,320 --> 00:24:05,840
is about to enter the Xingqiao relay satellite.

485
00:24:05,840 --> 00:24:06,840
What should we do?

486
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:10,140
So what are your thoughts?

487
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:14,520
I think we at least need to find someone

488
00:24:14,800 --> 00:24:16,120
to take his place.

489
00:24:16,560 --> 00:24:17,840
More than one helper,

490
00:24:17,840 --> 00:24:19,080
I found three for you.

491
00:24:19,720 --> 00:24:20,450
Which three?

492
00:24:20,680 --> 00:24:22,720
Those three rookies from the Muxing team.

493
00:24:22,720 --> 00:24:23,920
Mr. Qin, I'm serious.

494
00:24:23,920 --> 00:24:25,320
I'm not joking with you.

495
00:24:25,720 --> 00:24:26,560
The three of them

496
00:24:26,560 --> 00:24:28,000
haven't even passed their probation.

497
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:29,400
Two heads

498
00:24:29,400 --> 00:24:30,640
are better than one.

499
00:24:32,440 --> 00:24:34,300
I know you want to cultivate them,

500
00:24:34,480 --> 00:24:36,540
but our flight control has its rules.

501
00:24:36,840 --> 00:24:38,720
Previously it took at least a year and a half

502
00:24:38,720 --> 00:24:39,840
to enter a mission.

503
00:24:40,120 --> 00:24:41,840
Unless they make a special contribution,

504
00:24:41,840 --> 00:24:43,680
they can't become regular employees early.

505
00:24:43,680 --> 00:24:45,800
I do have a little idea.

506
00:24:47,080 --> 00:24:48,160
Look,

507
00:24:48,160 --> 00:24:49,280
come with me.

508
00:24:49,280 --> 00:24:49,880
Come.

509
00:24:50,080 --> 00:24:50,840
Where to?

510
00:24:51,200 --> 00:24:52,360
The office. Come.

511
00:25:01,280 --> 00:25:02,920
Put down the work at hand.

512
00:25:03,320 --> 00:25:04,520
Excuse me, everyone.

513
00:25:05,240 --> 00:25:06,800
Sit.

514
00:25:07,480 --> 00:25:08,720
Mr. Qin, you sit.

515
00:25:12,440 --> 00:25:13,280
Sit.

516
00:25:13,840 --> 00:25:14,840
It's nothing big.

517
00:25:15,200 --> 00:25:16,280
Let's talk about

518
00:25:16,280 --> 00:25:18,540
the center's recent work arrangements.

519
00:25:20,040 --> 00:25:22,720
I've seen Old Hou's review plan.

520
00:25:22,720 --> 00:25:23,800
Overall,

521
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:25,320
I'm not very satisfied.

522
00:25:26,240 --> 00:25:27,240
It must be redone.

523
00:25:27,920 --> 00:25:29,240
The importance of mission review,

524
00:25:29,240 --> 00:25:30,500
I believe you all know.

525
00:25:31,280 --> 00:25:33,680
You all must show a professional attitude.

526
00:25:33,720 --> 00:25:34,000
For the redo, Hangtian,

527
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:36,360
I hope the rookies can also participate.

528
00:25:42,040 --> 00:25:42,800
Well...

529
00:25:43,600 --> 00:25:45,320
They've been here less than a week.

530
00:25:45,320 --> 00:25:47,320
Doing both first launch and review...

531
00:25:47,320 --> 00:25:48,520
Isn't it too fast?

532
00:25:49,720 --> 00:25:49,920
Zhongguo Hangtian,

533
00:25:49,920 --> 00:25:51,480
are you afraid they'll surpass you?

534
00:25:51,480 --> 00:25:52,400
No.

535
00:25:52,880 --> 00:25:55,320
I just feel they haven't done it before.

536
00:25:55,400 --> 00:25:56,520
I'm afraid they won't do it well.

537
00:25:56,520 --> 00:25:58,800
Then pass your experience to them.

538
00:25:58,800 --> 00:25:59,680
As seniors,

539
00:25:59,680 --> 00:26:02,410
you should give young people chances to improve.

540
00:26:02,760 --> 00:26:03,360
Yes.

541
00:26:04,240 --> 00:26:05,600
Mr. Qin,

542
00:26:05,920 --> 00:26:07,080
about the review plan...

543
00:26:07,080 --> 00:26:08,320
If the three of us need

544
00:26:08,320 --> 00:26:09,780
to finish it ourselves...

545
00:26:10,440 --> 00:26:12,840
The main thing is we haven't done it before.

546
00:26:15,120 --> 00:26:16,120
China Aerospace.

547
00:26:17,880 --> 00:26:18,800
China Aerospace.

548
00:26:18,800 --> 00:26:18,920
China Aerospace.

549
00:26:18,920 --> 00:26:19,520
Jiajia,

550
00:26:19,520 --> 00:26:21,160
you arrange this part.

551
00:26:22,840 --> 00:26:23,770
That's settled.

552
00:26:24,920 --> 00:26:26,050
Meeting adjourned.

553
00:26:27,880 --> 00:26:28,240
Here,

554
00:26:28,240 --> 00:26:28,840
It's fine.

555
00:26:29,440 --> 00:26:30,300
take this back.

556
00:26:31,160 --> 00:26:32,360
I'll get back to work.

557
00:26:32,760 --> 00:26:33,440
Ying Ziqi,

558
00:26:33,680 --> 00:26:35,010
have you done it before?

559
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:36,000
No, I haven't.

560
00:26:36,560 --> 00:26:38,160
Reviews are usually conducted

561
00:26:38,160 --> 00:26:40,080
after major missions.

562
00:26:40,080 --> 00:26:41,120
In previous projects,

563
00:26:41,120 --> 00:26:42,360
we only made contingency plans.

564
00:26:42,360 --> 00:26:44,020
This is a bit difficult for us.

565
00:26:46,120 --> 00:26:47,600
We are dead this time.

566
00:26:48,960 --> 00:26:50,960
Don't say I didn't help you just now.

567
00:26:51,160 --> 00:26:52,290
I couldn't stop him.

568
00:26:52,720 --> 00:26:53,400
Alright.

569
00:26:53,520 --> 00:26:55,200
Don't worry too much.

570
00:26:55,640 --> 00:26:56,440
This idea

571
00:26:56,440 --> 00:26:58,920
was proposed by Qin for the first time.

572
00:26:59,280 --> 00:27:00,340
No one has tried it.

573
00:27:01,320 --> 00:27:01,840
You Xiu,

574
00:27:03,200 --> 00:27:05,800
you will be in charge of the newcomers' review.

575
00:27:09,640 --> 00:27:11,160
Get to work, senior.

576
00:27:11,160 --> 00:27:12,880
Why couldn't you stop him?

577
00:27:15,120 --> 00:27:16,640
Mr. Zhao is a veteran.

578
00:27:17,160 --> 00:27:17,720
You three,

579
00:27:17,720 --> 00:27:18,360
when you go in later,

580
00:27:18,360 --> 00:27:19,280
don't talk nonsense.

581
00:27:19,280 --> 00:27:20,880
I'll do the talking, hear me?

582
00:27:22,480 --> 00:27:23,760
Um, Mr. Zhao.

583
00:27:25,120 --> 00:27:25,960
Mr. Zhao.

584
00:27:26,880 --> 00:27:27,480
You...

585
00:27:28,200 --> 00:27:29,160
Hello, Mr. Zhao.

586
00:27:29,880 --> 00:27:31,640
Which department? Did you report?

587
00:27:31,640 --> 00:27:33,040
We're from the Flight Control Department.

588
00:27:33,040 --> 00:27:34,080
Due to work needs,

589
00:27:34,080 --> 00:27:36,080
we came to look up some information.

590
00:27:36,280 --> 00:27:36,880
Wu Wei.

591
00:27:37,640 --> 00:27:38,320
Wu Wei.

592
00:27:40,480 --> 00:27:43,760
Someone from the Flight Control Department is looking for you.

593
00:27:43,760 --> 00:27:44,440
Wei.

594
00:27:47,320 --> 00:27:48,120
Alright then.

595
00:27:48,120 --> 00:27:49,120
You three,

596
00:27:49,120 --> 00:27:50,200
look it up carefully later.

597
00:27:50,200 --> 00:27:52,160
I have something else to do, so I'll leave first.

598
00:27:52,160 --> 00:27:52,960
Archives guy,

599
00:27:53,400 --> 00:27:55,060
I'll leave these three to you.

600
00:27:56,280 --> 00:27:57,800
He's not called the archives guy.

601
00:27:57,800 --> 00:27:58,920
Call him Mr. Wu.

602
00:28:00,800 --> 00:28:02,280
Yes, Mr. Zhao.

603
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:04,160
Mr. Wu,

604
00:28:04,360 --> 00:28:05,890
sorry to trouble you later.

605
00:28:06,040 --> 00:28:06,970
I'm leaving now.

606
00:28:14,880 --> 00:28:15,400
Come on.

607
00:28:19,120 --> 00:28:20,160
A while ago, our archives

608
00:28:20,160 --> 00:28:21,200
digitally organized

609
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:22,530
the materials you need.

610
00:28:22,600 --> 00:28:23,800
They are mostly in this area,

611
00:28:23,800 --> 00:28:24,600
and that area.

612
00:28:24,600 --> 00:28:26,080
If there's something you really can't find,

613
00:28:26,080 --> 00:28:28,080
you can check the reference number on the computer.

614
00:28:28,080 --> 00:28:28,600
By the way.

615
00:28:28,600 --> 00:28:29,760
For the materials we need this time,

616
00:28:29,760 --> 00:28:30,760
I made a list.

617
00:28:30,840 --> 00:28:31,480
Nan.

618
00:28:31,920 --> 00:28:32,520
When did you

619
00:28:32,520 --> 00:28:33,760
make a list?

620
00:28:33,760 --> 00:28:34,960
Just now.

621
00:28:35,240 --> 00:28:37,680
It makes it easier to check for any missing items.

622
00:28:37,680 --> 00:28:38,540
So meticulous.

623
00:28:40,320 --> 00:28:41,360
Ying Ziqi, take a look

624
00:28:41,360 --> 00:28:42,200
and see if anything is missing.

625
00:28:42,200 --> 00:28:42,840
I won't look.

626
00:28:42,840 --> 00:28:44,900
Let's just search according to this.

627
00:28:45,360 --> 00:28:45,960
All right.

628
00:28:45,960 --> 00:28:47,520
I'm familiar with all the reference numbers.

629
00:28:47,520 --> 00:28:48,920
Let me help you find them.

630
00:28:50,280 --> 00:28:52,360
Then let's look at other materials too.

631
00:28:52,360 --> 00:28:54,220
Let's hurry up and find them then.

632
00:29:02,320 --> 00:29:03,520
By the way, Ying Ziqi.

633
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:05,000
Can we find some

634
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:07,640
previous rendezvous and docking materials as a reference?

635
00:29:07,640 --> 00:29:09,480
After all, if it's a review plan,

636
00:29:09,680 --> 00:29:11,440
we still need a general direction.

637
00:29:11,440 --> 00:29:13,800
This mission has new content added,

638
00:29:14,080 --> 00:29:16,740
so it might not be very similar to previous ones.

639
00:29:16,880 --> 00:29:17,760
We can focus on

640
00:29:17,760 --> 00:29:19,280
the plans from previous missions.

641
00:29:19,280 --> 00:29:20,800
I don't mind the direction.

642
00:29:20,800 --> 00:29:22,460
I'll follow everyone's lead.

643
00:29:23,920 --> 00:29:25,050
Let's listen to you.

644
00:29:25,240 --> 00:29:26,440
You are the backbone.

645
00:29:27,760 --> 00:29:28,880
Or we can listen to Nan.

646
00:29:28,880 --> 00:29:30,760
I will fully support you guys.

647
00:29:31,880 --> 00:29:32,640
How about this?

648
00:29:32,640 --> 00:29:33,720
Let's first follow

649
00:29:33,720 --> 00:29:34,840
the most conservative plan.

650
00:29:34,840 --> 00:29:35,840
What do you think?

651
00:29:36,040 --> 00:29:36,800
Sure.

652
00:29:42,680 --> 00:29:43,400
Look.

653
00:29:46,480 --> 00:29:47,800
It looks exactly the same on both sides.

654
00:29:47,800 --> 00:29:49,000
It's almost the same if you go this way.

655
00:29:49,000 --> 00:29:49,600
For your plan,

656
00:29:49,600 --> 00:29:52,130
which flight control stages does it involve?

657
00:29:58,480 --> 00:29:59,540
Wei, what's wrong?

658
00:30:01,920 --> 00:30:02,600
Nothing.

659
00:30:02,960 --> 00:30:05,160
I'll help you gather all the materials.

660
00:30:09,920 --> 00:30:11,200
There are still some parameters here,

661
00:30:11,200 --> 00:30:12,730
speed, ascent and descent.

662
00:30:40,120 --> 00:30:41,160
Are you done?

663
00:30:41,920 --> 00:30:42,480
Yes, done.

664
00:30:42,480 --> 00:30:43,120
Thanks.

665
00:30:43,600 --> 00:30:46,040
Do you want to go get something to eat together?

666
00:30:46,040 --> 00:30:46,800
You guys go ahead.

667
00:30:46,800 --> 00:30:48,130
I'm heading back first.

668
00:30:49,680 --> 00:30:50,560
Look at you,

669
00:30:50,560 --> 00:30:52,720
you're not active in work or socializing.

670
00:30:52,720 --> 00:30:55,280
Are we even done? You're in such a hurry to leave.

671
00:30:55,280 --> 00:30:56,480
Don't worry about it.

672
00:30:56,920 --> 00:30:58,580
You do it if you're so capable.

673
00:30:59,800 --> 00:31:01,200
He is still very reliable.

674
00:31:01,200 --> 00:31:04,060
We have already overfulfilled our tasks for today.

675
00:31:04,960 --> 00:31:05,520
Let's go, Nan.

676
00:31:05,520 --> 00:31:06,320
Let's go eat.

677
00:31:06,320 --> 00:31:07,240
I really don't want to hear the word

678
00:31:07,240 --> 00:31:08,160
'mission' today.

679
00:31:08,160 --> 00:31:09,040
We're here, okay.

680
00:31:09,040 --> 00:31:10,760
Okay, let's go.

681
00:31:12,280 --> 00:31:12,880
Wei,

682
00:31:12,880 --> 00:31:13,800
are you going?

683
00:31:14,760 --> 00:31:15,480
No, you guys go.

684
00:31:15,480 --> 00:31:16,740
I still have work to do.

685
00:31:17,320 --> 00:31:17,920
Okay.

686
00:31:19,160 --> 00:31:21,560
Finally off work. Time to eat.

687
00:32:54,320 --> 00:32:55,580
Why are you still here?

688
00:32:55,880 --> 00:32:57,340
What are you doing so late?

689
00:32:57,600 --> 00:32:59,800
I'm organizing some review materials.

690
00:32:59,920 --> 00:33:01,380
While sorting, I realized

691
00:33:01,640 --> 00:33:03,200
that our archives

692
00:33:03,200 --> 00:33:04,800
shouldn't just be organized by year

693
00:33:04,800 --> 00:33:06,200
or mission.

694
00:33:07,160 --> 00:33:09,160
They should be categorized by specific tasks.

695
00:33:09,160 --> 00:33:11,280
Take Longzhou, for example.

696
00:33:11,400 --> 00:33:13,040
This rendezvous and docking for Longzhou

697
00:33:13,040 --> 00:33:15,440
first appeared in the Fangzhou mission summary,

698
00:33:15,440 --> 00:33:17,970
and was also reflected in the Haoyue mission.

699
00:33:18,400 --> 00:33:19,680
If we only one-sidedly

700
00:33:19,680 --> 00:33:21,320
organize partial mission nodes,

701
00:33:21,320 --> 00:33:22,780
we'll still be in the dark.

702
00:33:29,400 --> 00:33:31,320
So what do you plan to do?

703
00:33:33,080 --> 00:33:34,880
Build a whole-system data model.

704
00:33:34,880 --> 00:33:36,440
Not just for one mission group.

705
00:33:36,440 --> 00:33:37,800
In the future, Fangzhou, Haoyue,

706
00:33:37,800 --> 00:33:39,200
Wentian, Longgong,

707
00:33:39,400 --> 00:33:40,600
will all be integrated into it.

708
00:33:40,600 --> 00:33:41,680
Turn our archives

709
00:33:41,680 --> 00:33:43,840
into a review database.

710
00:33:44,240 --> 00:33:46,360
We have so many good materials and papers.

711
00:33:46,360 --> 00:33:47,490
We can't waste them.

712
00:33:50,920 --> 00:33:51,800
That's great.

713
00:33:53,880 --> 00:33:55,800
But I think the workload

714
00:33:55,800 --> 00:33:57,440
is simply too massive.

715
00:33:57,560 --> 00:33:58,880
Take Fangzhou, for example.

716
00:33:58,880 --> 00:34:01,840
The optical communication system has been upgraded dozens of times alone.

717
00:34:01,840 --> 00:34:03,120
It's fine. I can handle it.

718
00:34:03,120 --> 00:34:03,680
Okay.

719
00:34:10,960 --> 00:34:12,120
How do you know

720
00:34:12,480 --> 00:34:15,080
such detailed things like how many times?

721
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:19,320
Well, I...

722
00:34:20,239 --> 00:34:22,719
I've been here for decades, after all.

723
00:34:25,040 --> 00:34:25,679
True.

724
00:34:26,159 --> 00:34:27,420
Let me tell you, Wu Wei,

725
00:34:28,280 --> 00:34:29,120
don't hold these materials

726
00:34:29,120 --> 00:34:30,600
so close to your eyes.

727
00:34:30,600 --> 00:34:31,960
It ruins your eyesight.

728
00:34:32,080 --> 00:34:32,600
Okay.

729
00:34:33,239 --> 00:34:33,880
All right.

730
00:34:33,880 --> 00:34:36,239
Turn off the lights and lock the door when you leave later.

731
00:34:36,239 --> 00:34:36,800
Got it.

732
00:35:28,600 --> 00:35:29,320
Today

733
00:35:29,320 --> 00:35:30,680
is my first time participating

734
00:35:30,680 --> 00:35:32,240
in an official flight control mission.

735
00:35:32,240 --> 00:35:33,800
I'd be lying if I said I wasn't nervous.

736
00:35:33,800 --> 00:35:34,960
My palms are sweaty.

737
00:35:34,960 --> 00:35:36,680
There was a little hiccup today,

738
00:35:36,680 --> 00:35:38,320
but fortunately it was handled quickly.

739
00:35:38,320 --> 00:35:39,360
Everyone was very cooperative.

740
00:35:39,360 --> 00:35:40,320
Today, the workshop director

741
00:35:40,320 --> 00:35:42,120
suddenly brought a guy with glasses to see me.

742
00:35:42,120 --> 00:35:43,120
He also brought a screw

743
00:35:43,120 --> 00:35:44,240
and asked if I could make one.

744
00:35:44,240 --> 00:35:45,480
It's a bit difficult,

745
00:35:45,480 --> 00:35:46,600
but not a big problem.

746
00:35:46,600 --> 00:35:48,120
I wouldn't brag about other things,

747
00:35:48,120 --> 00:35:49,680
but when it comes to lathe skills,

748
00:35:49,680 --> 00:35:51,210
I'm the best in the country.

749
00:35:51,360 --> 00:35:52,400
1969,

750
00:35:52,400 --> 00:35:53,960
April 20th,

751
00:35:53,960 --> 00:35:55,160
sunny.

752
00:35:55,680 --> 00:35:58,210
The sandstorm in Yangdaman is really fierce.

753
00:35:59,560 --> 00:36:02,090
The supply truck broke down on the road again.

754
00:36:02,360 --> 00:36:04,680
We haven't had meat for over ten days.

755
00:36:05,040 --> 00:36:07,640
The leader said we should improve our diet

756
00:36:07,640 --> 00:36:10,100
and told everyone to go catch fish together.

757
00:36:10,640 --> 00:36:12,100
He claimed to be an expert,

758
00:36:12,240 --> 00:36:14,080
but I didn't think he was.

759
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:15,720
After all that fuss,

760
00:36:15,720 --> 00:36:17,960
we only caught one small fish in the end.

761
00:36:19,280 --> 00:36:20,800
They still insist stubbornly

762
00:36:20,800 --> 00:36:22,760
that there's no problem with the theory

763
00:36:22,760 --> 00:36:24,600
and it's a method issue.

764
00:36:24,840 --> 00:36:26,000
In my opinion,

765
00:36:26,200 --> 00:36:28,040
they are mostly just bragging.

766
00:36:28,400 --> 00:36:29,760
So,

767
00:36:29,760 --> 00:36:31,480
you can't blindly trust authority;

768
00:36:31,480 --> 00:36:34,400
you must believe in science.

769
00:36:35,520 --> 00:36:37,480
April 24, 1970.

770
00:36:37,560 --> 00:36:39,360
The signals from Dongfanghong-1

771
00:36:39,360 --> 00:36:41,760
were also picked up by everyone today.

772
00:36:41,760 --> 00:36:43,240
Mr. Qian also came

773
00:36:43,240 --> 00:36:44,920
and specifically told me

774
00:36:44,920 --> 00:36:46,680
to study hard.

775
00:36:48,120 --> 00:36:50,680
Today is truly a day of double happiness.

776
00:36:51,120 --> 00:36:53,580
Let's have some meat and nourish ourselves.

777
00:36:54,040 --> 00:36:57,000
Today is the day I report to school.

778
00:36:57,640 --> 00:36:58,520
I never expected

779
00:36:58,520 --> 00:37:01,120
that I could actually become a college student

780
00:37:01,120 --> 00:37:03,040
to learn knowledge and culture.

781
00:37:03,840 --> 00:37:06,040
This is Jiuquan Launch Center.

782
00:37:06,720 --> 00:37:08,480
The time is now

783
00:37:08,480 --> 00:37:09,600
November 21, 1999,

784
00:37:09,600 --> 00:37:11,160
at 3:41 AM.

785
00:37:11,480 --> 00:37:12,520
Fangzhou-1,

786
00:37:12,680 --> 00:37:14,720
after a 21-hour flight,

787
00:37:14,720 --> 00:37:16,760
has successfully returned to Earth.

788
00:37:16,760 --> 00:37:17,560
Some say

789
00:37:17,760 --> 00:37:20,360
building missiles is worse than selling tea eggs.

790
00:37:20,360 --> 00:37:22,720
I, Zhao Qiangjun, don't believe this nonsense.

791
00:37:22,720 --> 00:37:24,640
Even if I'm broke my whole life,

792
00:37:24,640 --> 00:37:26,040
I still have to work hard.

793
00:37:26,120 --> 00:37:28,360
Good for you, Mr. Zhao,

794
00:37:29,160 --> 00:37:30,560
putting on an act with me.

795
00:37:39,320 --> 00:37:39,920
Wu Wei.

796
00:37:42,280 --> 00:37:42,920
Wu Wei!

797
00:37:45,440 --> 00:37:46,240
Where did this kid go?

798
00:37:46,240 --> 00:37:47,000
Mr. Zhao.

799
00:37:48,160 --> 00:37:49,040
I'm right here.

800
00:37:51,560 --> 00:37:52,890
You're good, young man.

801
00:37:53,760 --> 00:37:55,760
Good performance, very motivated.

802
00:37:56,000 --> 00:37:58,060
You even knew to get my package for me.

803
00:37:59,720 --> 00:38:00,520
How is it?

804
00:38:00,680 --> 00:38:02,480
How late did you work last night?

805
00:38:02,920 --> 00:38:03,760
Any progress?

806
00:38:05,640 --> 00:38:07,800
Progress is inevitable.

807
00:38:08,400 --> 00:38:09,360
But this package,

808
00:38:09,360 --> 00:38:11,020
I can't give it to you just yet.

809
00:38:11,320 --> 00:38:12,680
You brat, why?

810
00:38:14,360 --> 00:38:15,480
This rendezvous and docking

811
00:38:15,480 --> 00:38:17,560
microwave radar measurement data part,

812
00:38:17,560 --> 00:38:19,420
I studied it all night yesterday,

813
00:38:19,840 --> 00:38:21,500
but I still don't quite get it.

814
00:38:23,680 --> 00:38:24,800
You don't get it,

815
00:38:25,160 --> 00:38:26,360
so you think I do?

816
00:38:27,040 --> 00:38:28,760
I know you know.

817
00:38:29,440 --> 00:38:30,900
You don't have to act here.

818
00:38:31,360 --> 00:38:32,480
What am I acting?

819
00:38:32,480 --> 00:38:35,120
I'm just a logistics old man

820
00:38:35,120 --> 00:38:36,320
in the Space City.

821
00:38:37,760 --> 00:38:38,680
Really?

822
00:38:40,360 --> 00:38:41,490
Of course it's true.

823
00:38:43,880 --> 00:38:46,520
If you're going to hide it like this,

824
00:38:46,720 --> 00:38:48,400
I can only tell the truth.

825
00:38:50,960 --> 00:38:52,080
My grandfather

826
00:38:52,280 --> 00:38:54,880
is the national chess champion.

827
00:38:55,640 --> 00:38:57,600
With Mr. Qin's limited strength,

828
00:38:58,000 --> 00:39:01,320
if my grandfather just gives you a few pointers,

829
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:05,280
you'll dominate the chess games here

830
00:39:06,160 --> 00:39:07,420
with no problem at all.

831
00:39:15,600 --> 00:39:17,480
Can your grandfather really teach me?

832
00:39:17,480 --> 00:39:18,740
Just one word from him.

833
00:39:19,400 --> 00:39:22,800
As long as you give me a few pointers too.

834
00:39:23,360 --> 00:39:23,880
Okay.

835
00:39:26,880 --> 00:39:28,280
You can't fool me.

836
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:30,480
People in our Space City

837
00:39:30,720 --> 00:39:32,400
are all honest and trustworthy.

838
00:39:32,400 --> 00:39:33,280
Space folks

839
00:39:34,080 --> 00:39:35,480
don't lie to space folks.

840
00:39:38,640 --> 00:39:39,280
After you.

841
00:39:46,080 --> 00:39:46,800
Look.

842
00:39:56,960 --> 00:39:57,760
You brat.

843
00:39:57,760 --> 00:39:59,440
You finally remembered your grandfather.

844
00:39:59,440 --> 00:40:00,960
You don't even come back to visit.

845
00:40:00,960 --> 00:40:01,720
Old Wu.

846
00:40:02,600 --> 00:40:03,520
Emergency.

847
00:40:04,080 --> 00:40:05,480
Starting to learn chess.

848
00:40:05,760 --> 00:40:07,400
No, what do you mean?

849
00:40:07,760 --> 00:40:10,200
Are you trying to develop my brain

850
00:40:10,600 --> 00:40:12,840
because you're afraid I'll get dementia?

851
00:40:12,840 --> 00:40:13,760
Don't worry.

852
00:40:13,760 --> 00:40:15,320
I'm ranking up right now.

853
00:40:15,800 --> 00:40:17,560
Old Wu, stay out of this.

854
00:40:17,560 --> 00:40:20,320
It's all for your grandson's future anyway.

855
00:40:20,320 --> 00:40:22,200
What exactly are you doing?

856
00:40:22,760 --> 00:40:24,760
I'll tell you about it when I go back.

857
00:40:24,840 --> 00:40:25,400
Where is my dad?

858
00:40:25,400 --> 00:40:26,400
Okay, hold on.

859
00:40:28,640 --> 00:40:30,000
Your son is looking for you.

860
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:31,480
Tell him I'm not here.

861
00:40:32,480 --> 00:40:33,210
Your dad said

862
00:40:33,560 --> 00:40:34,360
he's not here.

863
00:40:35,880 --> 00:40:36,880
He is still angry.

864
00:40:37,160 --> 00:40:38,600
He is such a cheapskate.

865
00:40:38,600 --> 00:40:40,480
I'm telling you, he's so petty.

866
00:40:40,880 --> 00:40:42,680
Just take good care of yourself.

867
00:40:42,920 --> 00:40:43,600
You hear me?

868
00:40:44,320 --> 00:40:45,120
Okay, Grandpa.

869
00:40:45,120 --> 00:40:46,520
Everything is fine here.

870
00:40:47,000 --> 00:40:49,130
I'll go back and visit you in a few days.

871
00:40:49,240 --> 00:40:50,100
I'm hanging up.

872
00:40:52,520 --> 00:40:53,780
Does he need anything?

873
00:40:53,840 --> 00:40:55,300
How is he doing over there?

874
00:40:56,280 --> 00:40:57,210
I won't tell you.

875
00:40:58,600 --> 00:40:59,330
I'm leaving.

876
00:41:05,200 --> 00:41:06,520
No, do it again.

877
00:41:08,520 --> 00:41:10,120
Still don't know the reason?

878
00:41:11,920 --> 00:41:15,080
Is it because the data deduction is not accurate enough,

879
00:41:15,080 --> 00:41:17,600
or the backup plans are not enough?

880
00:41:17,800 --> 00:41:20,200
The point is you did a lot of unnecessary things,

881
00:41:20,200 --> 00:41:22,530
but basically none of the necessary ones.

882
00:41:25,320 --> 00:41:26,200
It's okay.

883
00:41:26,880 --> 00:41:27,920
It's everyone's first time.

884
00:41:27,920 --> 00:41:29,480
It'll be fine once you have experience.

885
00:41:29,480 --> 00:41:30,440
Since Mr. Chu

886
00:41:30,440 --> 00:41:31,600
has already reminded you,

887
00:41:31,600 --> 00:41:32,530
Go back and do it.

888
00:41:32,760 --> 00:41:33,720
Why are you still standing here?

889
00:41:33,720 --> 00:41:34,360
Ziqi.

890
00:41:35,120 --> 00:41:36,920
Caibao, take it more seriously.

891
00:41:38,400 --> 00:41:39,120
Mr. Chu.

892
00:41:40,120 --> 00:41:40,960
Demon King.

893
00:41:46,120 --> 00:41:46,920
Mr. Qin.

894
00:41:47,200 --> 00:41:49,530
There is something I want to report to you.

895
00:41:50,040 --> 00:41:51,400
Their review report,

896
00:41:51,400 --> 00:41:52,660
I have already read it.

897
00:41:52,720 --> 00:41:54,200
It's barely satisfactory.

898
00:41:54,200 --> 00:41:55,040
Qu Ruonan and Cai Bo'ao

899
00:41:55,040 --> 00:41:57,000
have not systematically understood the workflow.

900
00:41:57,000 --> 00:41:58,860
Only Ying Ziqi can barely keep up.

901
00:41:59,840 --> 00:42:01,480
I think the progress this time

902
00:42:01,480 --> 00:42:02,800
is a bit too fast for them.

903
00:42:02,800 --> 00:42:04,320
Otherwise, for this review work,

904
00:42:04,320 --> 00:42:05,560
let them do it with me.

905
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:09,160
We picked these people together.

906
00:42:09,920 --> 00:42:12,920
Everyone's advantages are quite obvious.

907
00:42:13,920 --> 00:42:15,200
But they all have problems.

908
00:42:15,200 --> 00:42:17,160
Xiao Qu has a solid foundation.

909
00:42:17,200 --> 00:42:19,600
But she is overcautious and lacks courage.

910
00:42:20,040 --> 00:42:21,640
Xiao Cai has the highest degree.

911
00:42:21,640 --> 00:42:23,520
But he is too young,

912
00:42:23,720 --> 00:42:24,920
lacking the ability to handle pressure.

913
00:42:24,920 --> 00:42:25,720
Actually, among them,

914
00:42:25,720 --> 00:42:28,250
the one I am least satisfied with is Ying Ziqi.

915
00:42:30,160 --> 00:42:31,640
He is the only one among the three

916
00:42:31,640 --> 00:42:34,170
with flight control internship experience.

917
00:42:35,040 --> 00:42:36,400
They have a solid foundation.

918
00:42:36,400 --> 00:42:38,160
But,

919
00:42:38,160 --> 00:42:40,220
they just want to slack off and coast.

920
00:42:40,600 --> 00:42:42,460
Their work attitude is a problem.

921
00:42:43,240 --> 00:42:44,680
How about

922
00:42:44,680 --> 00:42:45,960
we hold a meeting with them?

923
00:42:45,960 --> 00:42:48,160
If meetings worked, it would be easy.

924
00:42:50,640 --> 00:42:51,520
I have an idea.

925
00:42:52,480 --> 00:42:53,920
You'll find out in a couple of days.
